verses.text_plain: Praise ye the Lord. Praise ye the name of the Lord; praise him, O ye servants of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 1Praise ye the Lord. Praise ye the name of the Lord; praise him, O ye servants of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Ye that stand in the house of the Lord, in the courts of the house of our God,
verses.verse_html: 2Ye that stand in the house of the Lord, in the courts of the house of our God,

verses.text_plain: Praise the Lord; for the Lord is good: sing praises unto his name; for it is pleasant.
verses.verse_html: 3Praise the Lord; for the Lord is good: sing praises unto his name; for it is pleasant.

verses.text_plain: For the Lord hath chosen Jacob unto himself, and Israel for his peculiar treasure.
verses.verse_html: 4For the Lord hath chosen Jacob unto himself, and Israel for his peculiar treasure.

verses.text_plain: For I know that the Lord is great, and that our Lord is above all gods.
verses.verse_html: 5For I know that the Lord is great, and that our Lord is above all gods.

verses.text_plain: Whatsoever the Lord pleased, that did he in heaven, and in earth, in the seas, and all deep places.
verses.verse_html: 6Whatsoever the Lord pleased, that did he in heaven, and in earth, in the seas, and all deep places.

verses.text_plain: He causeth the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth; he maketh lightnings for the rain; he bringeth the wind out of his treasuries.
verses.verse_html: 7He causeth the vapours to ascend from the ends of the earth; he maketh lightnings for the rain; he bringeth the wind out of his treasuries.

verses.text_plain: Who smote the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and beast.
verses.verse_html:

verses.text_plain: Who sent tokens and wonders into the midst of thee, O Egypt, upon Pharaoh, and upon all his servants.
verses.verse_html: 9Who sent tokens and wonders into the midst of thee, O Egypt, upon Pharaoh, and upon all his servants.

verses.text_plain: Who smote great nations, and slew mighty kings;
verses.verse_html: 10Who smote great nations, and slew mighty kings;

verses.text_plain: Sihon king of the Amorites, and Og king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan:
verses.verse_html: 11Sihon king of the Amorites, and Og king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan:

verses.text_plain: And gave their land for an heritage, an heritage unto Israel his people.
verses.verse_html: 12And gave their land for an heritage, an heritage unto Israel his people.

verses.text_plain: Thy name, O Lord, endureth for ever; and thy memorial, O Lord, throughout all generations.
verses.verse_html:
13Thy name, O Lord, endureth for ever; and thy memorial, O Lord, throughout all generations. â–¼

verses.text_plain: For the Lord will judge his people, and he will repent himself concerning his servants.
verses.verse_html: 14For the Lord will judge his people, and he will repent himself concerning his servants.

verses.text_plain: The idols of the heathen are silver and gold, the work of menâ€™s hands.
verses.verse_html: 15The idols of the heathen are silver and gold, the work of menâ€™s hands.

verses.text_plain: They have mouths, but they speak not; eyes have they, but they see not;
verses.verse_html: 16They have mouths, but they speak not; eyes have they, but they see not;

verses.text_plain: They have ears, but they hear not; neither is there any breath in their mouths.
verses.verse_html: 17They have ears, but they hear not; neither is there any breath in their mouths.

verses.text_plain: They that make them are like unto them: so is every one that trusteth in them.
verses.verse_html: 18They that make them are like unto them: so is every one that trusteth in them.

verses.text_plain: Bless the Lord, O house of Israel: bless the Lord, O house of Aaron:
verses.verse_html: 19Bless the Lord, O house of Israel: bless the Lord, O house of Aaron:

verses.text_plain: Bless the Lord, O house of Levi: ye that fear the Lord, bless the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 20Bless the Lord, O house of Levi: ye that fear the Lord, bless the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Blessed be the Lord out of Zion, which dwelleth at Jerusalem. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 21Blessed be the Lord out of Zion, which dwelleth at Jerusalem. Praise ye the Lord.
